{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":597,"text":"One of my earliest memories"},{"time":2362,"text":"is of trying to wake up\none of my relatives and not being able to."},{"time":5482,"text":"And I was just a little kid,\nso I didn't really understand why,"},{"time":8459,"text":"but as I got older,"},{"time":9793,"text":"I realized we had\ndrug addiction in my family,"},{"time":11960,"text":"including later cocaine addiction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":13818,"text":"I'd been thinking about it a lot lately,\npartly because it's now exactly 100 years"},{"time":18621,"text":"since drugs were first banned\nin the United States and Britain,"},{"time":21691,"text":"and we then imposed that\non the rest of the world."},{"time":24230,"text":"It's a century since we made\nthis really fateful decision"},{"time":27750,"text":"to take addicts and punish them\nand make them suffer,"},{"time":31827,"text":"because we believed that would deter them;\nit would give them an incentive to stop."}]},{"cues":[{"time":36238,"text":"And a few years ago, I was looking at\nsome of the addicts in my life who I love,"},{"time":41231,"text":"and trying to figure out\nif there was some way to help them."},{"time":44644,"text":"And I realized there were loads\nof incredibly basic questions"},{"time":47918,"text":"I just didn't know the answer to,"},{"time":49752,"text":"like, what really causes addiction?"},{"time":52192,"text":"Why do we carry on with this approach\nthat doesn't seem to be working,"},{"time":55632,"text":"and is there a better way out there\nthat we could try instead?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":58561,"text":"So I read loads of stuff about it,"},{"time":60275,"text":"and I couldn't really find\nthe answers I was looking for,"},{"time":62966,"text":"so I thought, okay, I'll go and sit\nwith different people around the world"},{"time":66526,"text":"who lived this and studied this"},{"time":68214,"text":"and talk to them and see\nif I could learn from them."},{"time":70779,"text":"And I didn't realize I would end up\ngoing over 30,000 miles at the start,"},{"time":74280,"text":"but I ended up going and meeting\nloads of different people,"},{"time":77188,"text":"from a transgender crack dealer\nin Brownsville, Brooklyn,"},{"time":79967,"text":"to a scientist who spends a lot of time\nfeeding hallucinogens to mongooses"},{"time":83545,"text":"to see if they like them --"},{"time":84855,"text":"it turns out they do, but only\nin very specific circumstances --"},{"time":87960,"text":"to the only country that's ever\ndecriminalized all drugs,"},{"time":90755,"text":"from cannabis to crack, Portugal."},{"time":93134,"text":"And the thing I realized\nthat really blew my mind is,"},{"time":95735,"text":"almost everything we think\nwe know about addiction is wrong,"},{"time":99543,"text":"and if we start to absorb\nthe new evidence about addiction,"},{"time":102654,"text":"I think we're going to have to change\na lot more than our drug policies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":106100,"text":"But let's start with what we think\nwe know, what I thought I knew."},{"time":109525,"text":"Let's think about this middle row here."},{"time":111630,"text":"Imagine all of you, for 20 days now, went\noff and used heroin three times a day."},{"time":115416,"text":"Some of you look a little more\nenthusiastic than others at this prospect."},{"time":118885,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":119914,"text":"Don't worry,\nit's just a thought experiment."},{"time":122180,"text":"Imagine you did that, right?"},{"time":124243,"text":"What would happen?"},{"time":125428,"text":"Now, we have a story about what would\nhappen that we've been told for a century."},{"time":129245,"text":"We think, because there are\nchemical hooks in heroin,"},{"time":131766,"text":"as you took it for a while,"},{"time":133553,"text":"your body would become\ndependent on those hooks,"},{"time":136131,"text":"you'd start to physically need them,"},{"time":137919,"text":"and at the end of those 20 days,\nyou'd all be heroin addicts. Right?"},{"time":141267,"text":"That's what I thought."}]},{"cues":[{"time":142523,"text":"First thing that alerted me to the fact\nthat something's not right with this story"},{"time":146405,"text":"is when it was explained to me."},{"time":148083,"text":"If I step out of this TED Talk today\nand I get hit by a car and I break my hip,"},{"time":151822,"text":"I'll be taken to hospital\nand I'll be given loads of diamorphine."},{"time":155159,"text":"Diamorphine is heroin."},{"time":156745,"text":"It's actually much better heroin\nthan you're going to buy on the streets,"},{"time":160203,"text":"because the stuff you buy\nfrom a drug dealer is contaminated."},{"time":163159,"text":"Actually, very little of it is heroin,"},{"time":165007,"text":"whereas the stuff you get\nfrom the doctor is medically pure."},{"time":167847,"text":"And you'll be given it for quite\na long period of time."},{"time":170443,"text":"There are loads of people in this room,"},{"time":172325,"text":"you may not realize it,\nyou've taken quite a lot of heroin."},{"time":175310,"text":"And anyone who is watching this\nanywhere in the world, this is happening."},{"time":178887,"text":"And if what we believe\nabout addiction is right --"},{"time":181264,"text":"those people are exposed\nto all those chemical hooks --"},{"time":183860,"text":"What should happen?\nThey should become addicts."},{"time":186094,"text":"This has been studied really carefully."},{"time":188060,"text":"It doesn't happen; you will have noticed\nif your grandmother had a hip replacement,"},{"time":191989,"text":"she didn't come out as a junkie.\n(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":194037,"text":"And when I learned this,\nit seemed so weird to me,"},{"time":197650,"text":"so contrary to everything I'd been told,\neverything I thought I knew,"},{"time":201180,"text":"I just thought it couldn't be right,\nuntil I met a man called Bruce Alexander."},{"time":204995,"text":"He's a professor\nof psychology in Vancouver"},{"time":207617,"text":"who carried out an incredible experiment"},{"time":209556,"text":"I think really helps us\nto understand this issue."},{"time":211942,"text":"Professor Alexander explained to me,"},{"time":213704,"text":"the idea of addiction we've all\ngot in our heads, that story,"},{"time":216665,"text":"comes partly from a series of experiments"},{"time":218716,"text":"that were done earlier\nin the 20th century."},{"time":220826,"text":"They're really simple."},{"time":222156,"text":"You can do them tonight at home\nif you feel a little sadistic."},{"time":225160,"text":"You get a rat and you put it in a cage,\nand you give it two water bottles:"},{"time":228741,"text":"One is just water, and the other is water\nlaced with either heroin or cocaine."},{"time":232509,"text":"If you do that, the rat will almost always\nprefer the drug water"},{"time":235541,"text":"and almost always\nkill itself quite quickly."},{"time":237703,"text":"So there you go, right?\nThat's how we think it works."},{"time":240204,"text":"In the '70s, Professor Alexander comes\nalong and he looks at this experiment"},{"time":243800,"text":"and he noticed something."},{"time":245080,"text":"He said ah, we're putting\nthe rat in an empty cage."},{"time":247583,"text":"It's got nothing to do\nexcept use these drugs."},{"time":249840,"text":"Let's try something different."},{"time":251379,"text":"So Professor Alexander built a cage\nthat he called \"Rat Park,\""},{"time":254331,"text":"which is basically heaven for rats."},{"time":256871,"text":"They've got loads of cheese,\nthey've got loads of colored balls,"},{"time":259974,"text":"they've got loads of tunnels."},{"time":261382,"text":"Crucially, they've got loads of friends.\nThey can have loads of sex."},{"time":264597,"text":"And they've got both the water bottles,\nthe normal water and the drugged water."},{"time":269411,"text":"But here's the fascinating thing:"},{"time":272120,"text":"In Rat Park, they don't\nlike the drug water."},{"time":275602,"text":"They almost never use it."},{"time":277315,"text":"None of them ever use it compulsively."},{"time":279892,"text":"None of them ever overdose."},{"time":281317,"text":"You go from almost 100 percent overdose\nwhen they're isolated"},{"time":284731,"text":"to zero percent overdose when they\nhave happy and connected lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":287981,"text":"Now, when he first saw this,\nProfessor Alexander thought,"},{"time":291251,"text":"maybe this is just a thing about rats,\nthey're quite different to us."},{"time":294514,"text":"Maybe not as different as we'd like,\nbut, you know --"},{"time":297015,"text":"But fortunately, there was\na human experiment"},{"time":299150,"text":"into the exact same principle happening\nat the exact same time."},{"time":302279,"text":"It was called the Vietnam War."},{"time":304281,"text":"In Vietnam, 20 percent of all American\ntroops were using loads of heroin,"},{"time":308888,"text":"and if you look at the news\nreports from the time,"},{"time":311520,"text":"they were really worried, because\nthey thought, my God, we're going to have"},{"time":315202,"text":"hundreds of thousands of junkies\non the streets of the United States"},{"time":318426,"text":"when the war ends; it made total sense."},{"time":320366,"text":"Now, those soldiers who were using\nloads of heroin were followed home."},{"time":323676,"text":"The Archives of General Psychiatry\ndid a really detailed study,"},{"time":326654,"text":"and what happened to them?"},{"time":328582,"text":"It turns out they didn't go to rehab.\nThey didn't go into withdrawal."},{"time":332166,"text":"Ninety-five percent of them just stopped."},{"time":335476,"text":"Now, if you believe the story\nabout chemical hooks,"},{"time":337901,"text":"that makes absolutely no sense,\nbut Professor Alexander began to think"},{"time":341389,"text":"there might be a different\nstory about addiction."},{"time":343720,"text":"He said, what if addiction isn't\nabout your chemical hooks?"},{"time":346585,"text":"What if addiction is about your cage?"},{"time":349255,"text":"What if addiction is an adaptation\nto your environment?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":352393,"text":"Looking at this,"},{"time":353547,"text":"there was another professor\ncalled Peter Cohen in the Netherlands"},{"time":356669,"text":"who said, maybe we shouldn't\neven call it addiction."},{"time":359140,"text":"Maybe we should call it bonding."},{"time":360888,"text":"Human beings have a natural\nand innate need to bond,"},{"time":363811,"text":"and when we're happy and healthy,\nwe'll bond and connect with each other,"},{"time":367389,"text":"but if you can't do that,"},{"time":370043,"text":"because you're traumatized or isolated\nor beaten down by life,"},{"time":373867,"text":"you will bond with something\nthat will give you some sense of relief."},{"time":377190,"text":"Now, that might be gambling,\nthat might be pornography,"},{"time":379786,"text":"that might be cocaine,\nthat might be cannabis,"},{"time":381962,"text":"but you will bond and connect\nwith something because that's our nature."},{"time":385616,"text":"That's what we want as human beings."}]},{"cues":[{"time":388356,"text":"And at first, I found this quite\na difficult thing to get my head around,"},{"time":391868,"text":"but one way that helped me\nto think about it is,"},{"time":394323,"text":"I can see, I've got over by my seat\na bottle of water, right?"},{"time":397736,"text":"I'm looking at lots of you, and lots\nof you have bottles of water with you."},{"time":401284,"text":"Forget the drugs. Forget the drug war."},{"time":403123,"text":"Totally legally, all of those bottles\nof water could be bottles of vodka, right?"},{"time":407790,"text":"We could all be getting drunk --\nI might after this -- (Laughter) --"},{"time":411500,"text":"but we're not."},{"time":412676,"text":"Now, because you've been able to afford\nthe approximately gazillion pounds"},{"time":416177,"text":"that it costs to get into a TED Talk,\nI'm guessing you guys could afford"},{"time":419582,"text":"to be drinking vodka\nfor the next six months."},{"time":421960,"text":"You wouldn't end up homeless."},{"time":423931,"text":"You're not going to do that,\nand the reason you're not going to do that"},{"time":427556,"text":"is not because anyone's stopping you."},{"time":429459,"text":"It's because you've got\nbonds and connections"},{"time":431676,"text":"that you want to be present for."},{"time":433224,"text":"You've got work you love.\nYou've got people you love."},{"time":435725,"text":"You've got healthy relationships."},{"time":437770,"text":"And a core part of addiction,"},{"time":440440,"text":"I came to think, and I believe\nthe evidence suggests,"},{"time":442941,"text":"is about not being able to bear\nto be present in your life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":446779,"text":"Now, this has really\nsignificant implications."},{"time":449142,"text":"The most obvious implications\nare for the War on Drugs."},{"time":452300,"text":"In Arizona, I went out\nwith a group of women"},{"time":455860,"text":"who were made to wear t-shirts\nsaying, \"I was a drug addict,\""},{"time":459718,"text":"and go out on chain gangs and dig graves\nwhile members of the public jeer at them,"},{"time":464495,"text":"and when those women get out of prison,\nthey're going to have criminal records"},{"time":468195,"text":"that mean they'll never work\nin the legal economy again."},{"time":470839,"text":"Now, that's a very extreme example,\nobviously, in the case of the chain gang,"},{"time":474560,"text":"but actually almost\neverywhere in the world"},{"time":476650,"text":"we treat addicts to some degree like that."},{"time":478674,"text":"We punish them. We shame them.\nWe give them criminal records."},{"time":481556,"text":"We put barriers between them reconnecting."},{"time":484315,"text":"There was a doctor in Canada,\nDr. Gabor Maté, an amazing man,"},{"time":487318,"text":"who said to me, if you wanted to design\na system that would make addiction worse,"},{"time":491213,"text":"you would design that system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":492844,"text":"Now, there's a place that decided\nto do the exact opposite,"},{"time":495724,"text":"and I went there to see how it worked."},{"time":497581,"text":"In the year 2000, Portugal had\none of the worst drug problems in Europe."},{"time":501000,"text":"One percent of the population was addicted\nto heroin, which is kind of mind-blowing,"},{"time":504999,"text":"and every year, they tried\nthe American way more and more."},{"time":507791,"text":"They punished people and stigmatized them\nand shamed them more,"},{"time":510768,"text":"and every year, the problem got worse."},{"time":512611,"text":"And one day, the Prime Minister and\nthe leader of the opposition got together,"},{"time":516346,"text":"and basically said, look, we can't go on"},{"time":518349,"text":"with a country where we're having\never more people becoming heroin addicts."},{"time":521902,"text":"Let's set up a panel\nof scientists and doctors"},{"time":524085,"text":"to figure out what would\ngenuinely solve the problem."},{"time":526591,"text":"And they set up a panel led by\nan amazing man called Dr. João Goulão,"},{"time":529864,"text":"to look at all this new evidence,"},{"time":531514,"text":"and they came back and they said,"},{"time":533110,"text":"\"Decriminalize all drugs\nfrom cannabis to crack, but\" --"},{"time":537430,"text":"and this is the crucial next step --"},{"time":539724,"text":"\"take all the money we used to spend\non cutting addicts off,"},{"time":543369,"text":"on disconnecting them,"},{"time":544790,"text":"and spend it instead\non reconnecting them with society.\""},{"time":548454,"text":"And that's not really what we think of\nas drug treatment"},{"time":553050,"text":"in the United States and Britain."},{"time":554932,"text":"So they do do residential rehab,"},{"time":556537,"text":"they do psychological therapy,\nthat does have some value."},{"time":559369,"text":"But the biggest thing they did\nwas the complete opposite of what we do:"},{"time":562776,"text":"a massive program\nof job creation for addicts,"},{"time":565294,"text":"and microloans for addicts\nto set up small businesses."},{"time":567914,"text":"So say you used to be a mechanic."},{"time":569579,"text":"When you're ready, they'll go\nto a garage, and they'll say,"},{"time":572400,"text":"if you employ this guy for a year,\nwe'll pay half his wages."},{"time":575311,"text":"The goal was to make sure\nthat every addict in Portugal"},{"time":578068,"text":"had something to get out\nof bed for in the morning."},{"time":580473,"text":"And when I went and met the addicts\nin Portugal,"},{"time":583668,"text":"what they said is,\nas they rediscovered purpose,"},{"time":585946,"text":"they rediscovered bonds\nand relationships with the wider society."}]},{"cues":[{"time":589075,"text":"It'll be 15 years this year\nsince that experiment began,"},{"time":591719,"text":"and the results are in:"},{"time":593386,"text":"injecting drug use is down in Portugal,"},{"time":595268,"text":"according to the British\nJournal of Criminology,"},{"time":597883,"text":"by 50 percent, five-zero percent."},{"time":600470,"text":"Overdose is massively down,\nHIV is massively down among addicts."},{"time":604170,"text":"Addiction in every study\nis significantly down."},{"time":606545,"text":"One of the ways you know it's worked\nso well is that almost nobody in Portugal"},{"time":610408,"text":"wants to go back to the old system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":612113,"text":"Now, that's the political implications."},{"time":614001,"text":"I actually think there's a layer\nof implications"},{"time":617024,"text":"to all this research below that."},{"time":618684,"text":"We live in a culture where people\nfeel really increasingly vulnerable"},{"time":621970,"text":"to all sorts of addictions,\nwhether it's to their smartphones"},{"time":624950,"text":"or to shopping or to eating."},{"time":626308,"text":"Before these talks began --\nyou guys know this --"},{"time":628639,"text":"we were told we weren't allowed\nto have our smartphones on,"},{"time":631503,"text":"and I have to say, a lot of you\nlooked an awful lot like"},{"time":634148,"text":"addicts who were told their dealer\nwas going to be unavailable"},{"time":637157,"text":"for the next couple of hours. (Laughter)"},{"time":639086,"text":"A lot of us feel like that,\nand it might sound weird to say,"},{"time":641957,"text":"I've been talking about how disconnection\nis a major driver of addiction"},{"time":645374,"text":"and weird to say it's growing,"},{"time":646827,"text":"because you think we're the most connected\nsociety that's ever been, surely."},{"time":650423,"text":"But I increasingly began to think\nthat the connections we have"},{"time":653480,"text":"or think we have, are like a kind\nof parody of human connection."},{"time":656504,"text":"If you have a crisis in your life,\nyou'll notice something."},{"time":659365,"text":"It won't be your Twitter followers\nwho come to sit with you."},{"time":662299,"text":"It won't be your Facebook friends\nwho help you turn it round."},{"time":665181,"text":"It'll be your flesh and blood friends\nwho you have deep and nuanced"},{"time":668348,"text":"and textured, face-to-face\nrelationships with,"},{"time":670614,"text":"and there's a study I learned about from\nBill McKibben, the environmental writer,"},{"time":675173,"text":"that I think tells us a lot about this."},{"time":677380,"text":"It looked at the number of close friends\nthe average American believes"},{"time":680778,"text":"they can call on in a crisis."},{"time":682729,"text":"That number has been declining\nsteadily since the 1950s."},{"time":685747,"text":"The amount of floor space\nan individual has in their home"},{"time":688621,"text":"has been steadily increasing,"},{"time":690688,"text":"and I think that's like a metaphor"},{"time":692592,"text":"for the choice we've made as a culture."},{"time":694474,"text":"We've traded floorspace for friends,\nwe've traded stuff for connections,"},{"time":699349,"text":"and the result is we are one of the\nloneliest societies there has ever been."},{"time":702970,"text":"And Bruce Alexander, the guy who did\nthe Rat Park experiment, says,"},{"time":706161,"text":"we talk all the time in addiction\nabout individual recovery,"},{"time":709732,"text":"and it's right to talk about that,"},{"time":711659,"text":"but we need to talk much more\nabout social recovery."},{"time":714214,"text":"Something's gone wrong with us,\nnot just with individuals but as a group,"},{"time":717867,"text":"and we've created a society where,\nfor a lot of us,"},{"time":720300,"text":"life looks a whole lot more\nlike that isolated cage"},{"time":722785,"text":"and a whole lot less like Rat Park."}]},{"cues":[{"time":724856,"text":"If I'm honest, this isn't\nwhy I went into it."},{"time":727912,"text":"I didn't go in to the discover\nthe political stuff, the social stuff."},{"time":731242,"text":"I wanted to know how to help\nthe people I love."},{"time":733605,"text":"And when I came back from this\nlong journey and I'd learned all this,"},{"time":736868,"text":"I looked at the addicts in my life,"},{"time":739600,"text":"and if you're really candid,\nit's hard loving an addict,"},{"time":744130,"text":"and there's going to be lots of people\nwho know in this room."},{"time":747012,"text":"You are angry a lot of the time,"},{"time":749260,"text":"and I think one of the reasons\nwhy this debate is so charged"},{"time":753285,"text":"is because it runs through the heart\nof each of us, right?"},{"time":756109,"text":"Everyone has a bit of them\nthat looks at an addict and thinks,"},{"time":759080,"text":"I wish someone would just stop you."},{"time":760855,"text":"And the kind of scripts we're told for how\nto deal with the addicts in our lives"},{"time":764641,"text":"is typified by, I think,"},{"time":765837,"text":"the reality show \"Intervention,\"\nif you guys have ever seen it."},{"time":768814,"text":"I think everything in our lives\nis defined by reality TV,"},{"time":771512,"text":"but that's another TED Talk."},{"time":772981,"text":"If you've ever seen\nthe show \"Intervention,\""},{"time":775193,"text":"it's a pretty simple premise."},{"time":776673,"text":"Get an addict, all the people\nin their life, gather them together,"},{"time":779793,"text":"confront them with what they're doing,\nand they say, if you don't shape up,"},{"time":783449,"text":"we're going to cut you off."},{"time":784811,"text":"So what they do is they take\nthe connection to the addict,"},{"time":787550,"text":"and they threaten it,\nthey make it contingent"},{"time":789670,"text":"on the addict behaving the way they want."},{"time":792072,"text":"And I began to think, I began to see\nwhy that approach doesn't work,"},{"time":795823,"text":"and I began to think that's almost like\nthe importing of the logic of the Drug War"},{"time":800397,"text":"into our private lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":802278,"text":"So I was thinking,\nhow could I be Portuguese?"},{"time":805970,"text":"And what I've tried to do now,\nand I can't tell you I do it consistently"},{"time":809499,"text":"and I can't tell you it's easy,"},{"time":811472,"text":"is to say to the addicts in my life"},{"time":813980,"text":"that I want to deepen\nthe connection with them,"},{"time":816230,"text":"to say to them, I love you\nwhether you're using or you're not."},{"time":819924,"text":"I love you, whatever state you're in,"},{"time":822780,"text":"and if you need me,\nI'll come and sit with you"},{"time":825195,"text":"because I love you and I don't\nwant you to be alone"},{"time":827819,"text":"or to feel alone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":829839,"text":"And I think the core of that message --"},{"time":831905,"text":"you're not alone, we love you --"},{"time":834598,"text":"has to be at every level\nof how we respond to addicts,"},{"time":837687,"text":"socially, politically and individually."},{"time":840334,"text":"For 100 years now, we've been singing\nwar songs about addicts."},{"time":844606,"text":"I think all along we should have been\nsinging love songs to them,"},{"time":848530,"text":"because the opposite of addiction\nis not sobriety."},{"time":852802,"text":"The opposite of addiction is connection."}]},{"cues":[{"time":856657,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":858630,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}